HEADWORD: Lurry
<hw>Lur"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>llwry</ets>
precipitant, a provision.]</ety> <def>A confused heap; a throng, as of
persons; a jumble, as of sounds.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To turn prayer into a kind of <qex>lurry</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luscinia</ent>⟦br⟧
